  "description": {
    "en-US": "Travel phrases for Malaysia with audio, built for Grab rides, Touch 'n Go payments, hotel check-ins, food courts, mamak stops, and everyday travel requests.",
    "zh-CN": "马来西亚旅行短语卡，围绕 Grab 打车、Touch 'n Go 支付、酒店入住、食阁和 mamak 餐馆等高频落地场景整理。"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en-US": "Built for Malaysia trips where airport transfers, mall pickups, food-court orders, and hotel counters can all happen in a single afternoon. These cards help when you need quick Malay for Grab pickup points, Touch 'n Go questions, halal requests, or simple service interactions without typing into a translator.",
    "zh-CN": "这套马来西亚短语适合那种机场接驳、商场上车点、食阁点单和酒店柜台会连续出现的旅行节奏。遇到要确认 Grab 上车点、Touch 'n Go、清真需求，或者只想快速说明一个简单请求时，短语卡会比临时打翻译更顺手。"
  },
  "teaser": {
    "en-US": "Built for Malaysia arrivals, Touch 'n Go questions, Grab rides, food courts, and late-night mamak stops.",
    "zh-CN": "适合马来西亚落地后的 Touch 'n Go、Grab、食阁和深夜 mamak 餐馆沟通。"
  },
  "travelTips": {
    "en-US": [
      "Keep short phrases ready for Grab pickups, station questions, and Touch 'n Go top-ups because transport and payment happen quickly in Kuala Lumpur.",
      "Dining phrases are especially helpful in food courts and mamak spots where you may need to ask about spice, takeaway, or whether a dish is halal.",
      "English works in many places, but a visible phrase card still helps when the counter is noisy or the queue is moving fast."
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "在吉隆坡这类城市里，Grab 上车点、车站问路和 Touch 'n Go 充值最好提前备好几句常用短语。",
      "食阁和 mamak 餐馆点单时，餐饮短语特别实用，尤其是确认辣度、打包带走或是否清真这类问题。",
      "虽然很多地方能用英语，但柜台嘈杂或排队很快时，直接展示短语卡还是会更高效。"
    ]
  },
  "highlights": {
    "en-US": [
      "Touch 'n Go and mamak stops",
      "Grab pickups and food courts",
      "Hotels, halal requests, and mall directions"
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "Touch 'n Go 与 mamak 餐馆",
      "Grab 上车点与食阁沟通",
      "酒店、清真需求与商场问路"
    ]
  },
