  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrase groups matter most for a first trip to Malaysia?",
        "zh-CN": "第一次去马来西亚旅行，最值得先准备哪几组短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Start with transport, dining, and hotel. That covers airport transfers, Grab rides, Touch 'n Go, check-in, and most food-court conversations on day one.",
        "zh-CN": "建议先看交通、餐饮和酒店三组，基本就能覆盖机场接驳、Grab、Touch 'n Go、入住办理，以及第一天大部分食阁点单场景。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Do I need Malay if many people speak English in Malaysia?",
        "zh-CN": "马来西亚很多地方能讲英语，还需要准备马来语短语吗？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "A little Malay still helps for transport, food courts, and smaller counters. Short phrase cards are especially useful when you want to move fast without re-explaining the same request.",
        "zh-CN": "还是有帮助，尤其是在交通、食阁和一些小柜台场景里。备几张简短短语卡，很多时候能让你不用重复解释同一个需求。"
      }
    }
  ]
}
